 Their average kinetic energy is smaller. 

00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:58.100
 This does not mean that each of these molecules 

00:03:58.110 --> 00:04:00.110
 is slower than any of the molecules in the first system, 

00:04:00.110 --> 00:04:02.160
 or has less kinetic energy than it. 

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:06.760
 But the average kinetic energy of these is smaller. 

00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:08.920
 We can draw a distribution curve. 

00:04:08.930 --> 00:04:10.600
 We call that 

00:04:10.600 --> 00:04:13.382
 distribution of Maxwell-Boltzmann. 

00:04:13.382 --> 00:04:15.110
 Let's do it. 

00:04:15.110 --> 00:04:18.700
 We draw a coordinate system. 

00:04:18.840 --> 00:04:23.840
 This is mine. 

00:04:23.920 --> 00:04:28.160
 On this axis I will display the speed. 

00:04:28.300 --> 00:04:30.140
 Like this. 

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:33.532
 And the other axis will be the number of molecules. 

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:39.720
 Number of molecules here. 

00:04:39.800 --> 00:04:43.020
 For the first system, which is at 300 Kelvin, 

00:04:43.020 --> 00:04:46.092
 distribution may look like this. 

